{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3156695,"name":"gadyh","username":"gadyh","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/b487fb/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-03-03T20:13:10.412Z","cooked":"

We have a problem while trying to machine an extrusion in our cnc router.

We have a X:60cm Y:90cm machine, and we are trying to machine a 70cm extrusion.
We are using artcam for creating the gcodes.

The pocketing went well, but when we tried to work on the extrusion itself, weve got a “X- out of soft limit” problem.

It is very strange since the extrusion is positioned along the Y axis, and we programmed it alomg the same axis.

What could be the solutions?

Also, i said, we could make the pocket in the wood for the extrusion for positioning it.

When we tried to start the same program but shorter, it ran on the X axis instead of the Y axis.
It looks like for some eeason the two axis get swapped somewhere
